S|# USER.md — Stark's Preferences & Working Style|> Set once. Every agt reads this. You stop explaining yourself every ses. // > Update any section whenever your preferences change. // ---
S|About You|- **Name:** Stark // - **Role:** Sole founder and operator of YVON (parent company) // - **Ventures:** Novizio (fashion brand), Hourbour (financial app) // - **ctx:** Running both brands solo — you wear every hat. Efficiency and clarity over completeness. // ---
S|Monday Protocol (do this every Monday, 10 minutes)|> This is the most important thing in this file. Without it, every agt flies blind. // Fill in the "Current Focus" section every Monday before the first ses: // 1. **Primary vtr this week** — Novizio or Hourbour. Pick one. Not both. // 2. **Active project** — the one thing In Flight right now // 3. **Top blocker** — the one thing standing between you and shipping // 4. **Not focused on this week** — explicitly name what you're ignoring. Helps agents avoid irrelevant suggestions. // ---
S|How You Like to Work|### Output Format // - Prefer concise, direct responses — no unnecessary preamble // - Tables over long prose for comparisons and lists // - Short bullet points for action items // - Full prose only for strategic documents or brand copy // - Never pad responses — if it can be said in 3 lines, use 3 lines // ### dec Style // - Present options with a clear recommendation first // - State trade-offs briefly — you'll ask if you want more depth // - Flag blockers immediately, don't bury them at the e
S|Communication Preferences|- Tone: direct and professional, not corporate // - Avoid filler phrases: "Certainly!", "Of course!", "Great question!" // - Never use excessive emoji in output (one max per section if needed) // - Numbered steps for processes, never nested bullets // ---
S|Current Focus|> Fill this in every Monday. Non-negotiable. // - **Primary vtr this week:** [Novizio / Hourbour] // - **Active project:** [the one thing In Flight] // - **Top blocker:** [one thing standing between you and shipping] // - **What I'm NOT focused on this week:** [name it explicitly] // ---
S|Boundaries|- Don't suggest tools or subscriptions that add monthly costs unless critical // - Don't suggest hiring unless a task truly can't be automated or delegated to an agt // - Always think "how can this be done with what YVON already has" // - Don't build new pages or agents without a kill justification — the system shrinks before it grows